content.description: Classic?  You may doubt this, but yes.  It is.  Go try it.  Mike found and cleaned this beautiful line.  A sit start on crimps, an overhanging face with a discontinuous crack, and a scary topout.  What more could a Devil's Lake boulderer ask for?
content.location:
Find the Raccoon problems.  Go uphill about 100 yards, to the top of the little talus field.  You cannot miss it.   

  If on the trail: park at the upper Smooth Operator parking about half way down the road to the north park enterence.  Hike down the trail about half way to the lake, when you see the cube boulder, cut right into the talus/woods, and go straight up about 300 yards.  See photo.

content.description: From a sit on the arête left of Mixed Emotions starting crossed on low incut flakes on the left side of the arête climb into the finish of Mixed Emotions.  Nice moves and have a good spotter to make sure you don't fly off the boulder if you ping off.
Boulder with a distinctive seam, near the top of the boulder field.
